    This is a file to get synthetic series generated by Streamflow Generator code execution, change the daily data to accumulated weekly data and join them with the historical observations. The input are the 'historical' and 'synthetic' folder from the 'Kirsch-Nowak_Streamflow_Generator-master' directory.
---
```{r setup, include=FALSE}
knitr::opts_chunk$set(echo = TRUE)
```


```{r}
setwd("E:/UNB/Projeto/PRGroup/series_sinteticas/streamflow_generator/ajuste_formato_para_WaterPaths") #diretory definition, should be changed for new applications
options(scipen=999)
```

```{r}
library(forecast)
require(tseries)
library(readr)
require(tidyverse)
library(lubridate)
library(aweek)
library(readxl)
library(readr)
```
  The sim file is on the same directory as this R file, and contains the ID for each synthetic serie (example: if there are 1,000 synthetic series, the file should have an enumaration from 1 to 1,000, each number on one row. This should be changed according to the amount of synthetic series generated on Streamflow generator)
```{r}
sim <- read_excel("sim.xlsx")
```

Synthetic series treatment
```{r}
files_to_read = list.files(
  path = "E:/UNB/Projeto/PRGroup/series_sinteticas/streamflow_generator/Kirsch-Nowak_Streamflow_Generator-master/validation/synthetic", #should change for new applications, to the directory where the synthetic daily series from Streamflow generator process were saved
  pattern = ".*(-1000x40-daily).*csv$", # should change for the extension of the files names (example: '-2000x50-monthly' - 2000, 50 year long, synthetic series, this comes automatically with Streamflow generator code execution)
  recursive = TRUE,          
  full.names = TRUE          
)
```

Historical data treatment
Important to notice that the historical data used in this study was in m/s for inflows and mm/day for evaporation. Thus, the synthetic data generated by Streamflow Generator maintained these units. For WaterPaths, the data must be in hm/week for inflow and hm/week for evaporation
